Class solverOutput

java.lang.Object
dataTypes.solverOutput
public class solverOutput
extends java.lang.Object
Represents output of an optimization solver.
Author:
Sudesh Agrawal (sudesh@utexas.edu). Last Updated: September 22, 2020.

    • solverOptionsUsed

      java.util.Map<java.lang.String,​java.lang.String> solverOptionsUsed
      Solver options (tolerance, iteration limit, etc.) used in optimization. Allowed solver options:
      IntFeasTol
      integer feasibility tolerance
      MIPGap
      current relative MIP optimality gap
      threads
      number of threads to apply to parallel algorithms
      Presolve
      controls the presolve level
      TimeLimit
      limits the total time expended (in seconds).

    • solverMessage

      java.lang.String solverMessage
      Solver message (generally indicating the solver status).
